- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about developing a novel attention model for dependency parsing, which is a subfield of natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning model for dependency parsing.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing an intelligent system for parsing natural language sentences.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for the proposed model.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses continuous embeddings for headwords, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision and natural language processing.
